review_text: I have been a customer of Union saving since the bank moved into town  The  people that worked there were great but now the  new management leaves a lot to be desired .  I needed a certain seal for some papers, I was told it would cost me $ 20.00 and I had to show probate papers and death certificate which really had me wondering why. I went to People's United where I have another account and they did what I needed with just a ID and no charge .  Union savings bank is not what it use to be. I will be looking into changing banks
Use to think this was a nice small town bank, now that they want to charge me $5 to cash my paycheck I realized it is just another blood sucking bank that doesn't care about people.
